channel.title: Whats more efficient
channel.description:
i have a ton of objects i want to store in an array/2darray
what's more memmory efficient
Object[X][Y]
or
Object[X<<16 + Y] ?

item.title: Whats more efficient
item.dc:creator: @abraham2119 abraham2119
item.description:
@abraham2119 wrote:

[quote=“oksuper_, post:11, topic:324776”][quote author=pplsuqbawlz link=topic=421127.msg3093908#msg3093908 date=1263114737]
An array in native languages are actually just blocks of memory where an array accesses that block via mov etc… where the pointer is the offset of the block + index… As apposed to java, where an array is an Object there in of itself used to manage a series of other objects, given a new object for each instance inside of a sub dimension… It adds up.

Simple answer: USE THE FUCKING 1 DIMENSIONAL JUST LIKE FRANK_ SAYS. BTW, ITS NOT JUST A 2 DIMENSIONAL SOLUTION… YOU CAN USE 1 DIMENSIONAL ARRAYS TO HOLD INDEFINATE AMOUNTS OF DIMENSIONAL DATA; JUST LEARN ALGEBRA & CALCULUS DUDE.

As far as I know this should work: z * (w * h) + y * w + x
[/quote]

thank you for your redundant information that we already knew and your expression for calculating a 3d index into a 1d array[/quote]+1

Read full topic
